    <note type="biography">
        <p>German-born botanist. Accompanied his brother, Robert Hermann Schomburgk, as botanist to the British Guiana boundary survey, 1840–4; published an account of the boundary expedition, 1847. After political troubles in Germany, he fled to Australia in 1849. Curator of the Adelaide Botanic Garden, South Australia, from 1865.</p></note>
